V0405_01_00_01_0.text: Write it in pen instead of pencil that you're gonna lose!

V0405_01_00_02_0.text: Yuma would never turn down a Duel, so I won't either!

V0405_01_00_03_0.text:
Duel Disk, go!!!
Duel Gazer, let's roll!!!

V0405_01_00_04_0.text: I'm gonna extend your losing streak, Yuma!

V0405_01_00_05_0.text:
Astral!
I've memorized every card in Yuma's deck!

V0405_01_00_06_0.text: Shark might be tough, but I'm no slouch!

V0405_01_00_08_0.text: If you want a Number, then defeat me in a Duel!

V0405_01_00_09_0.text:
Hey uh Rio...
You uh, like, want to Duel?

V0405_03_00_01_0.text: I've had leads vanish, so I can't let my guard down!

V0405_03_00_05_0.text: This is bad, but I'm not givin' up!

V0405_07_09_00_0.text: I'm flippin' over my Set card!

V0405_08_00_00_0.text: I activate the Spell Card, Iron Call!

V0405_08_00_00_1.text: It revives a Level 4 or lower Machine from the Graveyard!

V0405_08_00_01_0.text:
I activate my Spell Card!
Iron Draw!

V0405_08_00_01_1.text: I have 2 Machine Effect Monsters in play, so I draw 2 cards!

V0405_08_00_02_0.text: I activate my Spell, Monster Reborn!

V0405_08_00_03_0.text: I activate my Quick-Play Spell, Rush Recklessly!

V0405_08_00_03_1.text: The monster I choose gains 700 ATK!

V0405_08_00_04_0.text: I activate my Continuous Spell, Machine Assembly Line!

V0405_08_00_05_0.text: Machine Assembly Line revives a Machine monster!

V0405_08_00_05_1.text: If its Level is equal or less than the Junk Counters!

V0405_08_00_06_0.text:
I activate my Quick-Play Spell!
Limiter Removal!

V0405_08_00_07_0.text: I activate the Continuous Trap, Call of the Haunted!

V0405_08_00_08_0.text: I activate the Quick-Play Spell, Geargia Change!

V0405_08_00_09_0.text:
I activate my Trap Card!
Geargiagear!

V0405_08_00_09_1.text: I Special Summon two Geargianos from my deck!

V0405_08_00_10_0.text:
I activate my Continuous Spell!
Wind-Up Factory!

V0405_08_00_11_1.text: I add a Wind-Up monster in my deck to my hand!

V0405_08_00_12_0.text: I activate the Quick-Play Spell, Legendary Wind-Up Key!

V0405_08_00_12_1.text: My Wind-Up monsters switch to face-down Defense Position!

V0405_08_00_13_0.text:
I activate my Spell Card!
Zenmailfunction!

V0405_08_00_13_1.text: I resurrect a Wind-Up from my Graveyard in Defense Position!

V0405_08_00_14_0.text:
I activate my Spell Card!
Weights & Zenmaisures!

V0405_08_00_15_0.text:
I activate my Trap Card!
Overwind!

V0405_08_00_15_1.text: My Wind-Up monster's ATK and DEF are doubled!

V0405_08_00_16_0.text: I activate my Continuous Trap, Zenmaiday!

V0405_09_00_01_1.text: It gains 400 ATK once per turn!

V0405_09_00_02_0.text: Gearspring Spirit lowers your monster's ATK to 0!

V0405_09_00_03_1.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to switch your monster's position!

V0405_09_00_04_0.text: This lets me Special Summon a Level 4 monster from my hand!

V0405_09_00_05_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to activate Shining Elf's effect!

V0405_09_00_06_1.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to return that monster to the deck!

V0405_09_00_07_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to activate Utopia's effect!

V0405_09_00_08_0.text: I discard a Machine to activate Shreddder's effect!

V0405_09_00_08_1.text: It destroys your monster with equal or lower Level!

V0405_09_00_18_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to use Geargiagear Gigant XG's effect!

V0405_09_00_19_0.text: When Gigant XG leaves the field, its effect activates!

V0405_09_00_20_0.text: For 1 Overlay Unit, I can activate Gear Gigant X's effect!

V0405_09_00_21_0.text: Gear Gigant X left the field, so its effect activates!

V0405_09_00_23_0.text: When a Wind-Up monster is summoned, I can bring this out!

V0405_09_00_28_0.text: Wind-Up Knight is using its effect!

V0405_09_00_32_0.text: Wind-Up Honeybee's effect activates when it's destroyed!

V0405_09_00_37_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to activate Zenmaister's effect!

V0405_09_00_39_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to activate Zenmaity's effect!

V0405_09_00_40_0.text: I use 1 Overlay Unit to activate Zenmaioh's effect!

V0405_11_01_00_0.text: I Summon a monster in Defense Position!

V0405_11_08_01_0.text:
I build the Overlay Network!
Xyz Summon!

V0405_37_00_00_0.text: I overlay two Level 2's to Xyz Summon!

V0405_37_00_01_0.text:
Do I have two Level 4 monsters...? I do!
I Xyz Summon!

V0405_37_00_02_0.text: I'll use three Level 1 monsters to Xyz Summon!

V0405_13_00_08_1.text:
W-Whoa!
I never knew Numbers were this powerful!

V0405_13_00_24_0.text: Wind-Up Soldier is here to battle!

V0405_13_00_32_0.text: Wind-Up Snail is slowly making its way here!

V0405_13_00_35_0.text:
Wind-Up Zenmaister!
I'm countin' on ya!

V0405_37_00_03_0.text: I have two Level 3 monsters, so I can Xyz Summon!

V0405_13_00_36_0.text: Don't let me down, Wind-Up Zenmaines!

V0405_13_00_38_0.text: Let's do this, Wind-Up Arsenal Zenmaioh!

V0405_19_00_08_0.text:
This is how I high five the sky!
Utopia! Attack!

V0405_19_00_32_0.text:
Wind-Up Snail!
You can take your time, but attack!

V0405_21_00_02_0.text: That brings my turn to an end!

V0405_28_00_00_0.text: If losing brings the waterworks, try harder next time!

V0405_28_00_01_0.text:
You won't defeat me!
Not now, not ever!

V0405_28_00_02_0.text: You're throwin' in the towel already?

V0405_28_00_04_0.text: You should try this thing called strategy next time.

V0405_28_00_05_0.text:
Feel the flow?
More like feel the no.

V0405_28_00_06_0.text:
I did it!
I defeated Quattro!

V0405_28_00_07_0.text: Rio, I hope you'll Duel me again soon!

V0405_29_00_01_0.text: This loss has me down in the dumps...

V0405_29_00_04_0.text:
Yuma!
You created an amazing combo!

V0405_29_00_04_1.text: ...Or did Astral come up with it?

V0405_29_00_05_0.text: You're a lot tougher than you used to be, Yuma!

V0405_29_00_07_0.text:
Rio, I'm gonna get stronger!
A lot stronger!
Just you watch!

V0405_29_00_08_0.text: Rio's scary when she's tough, but that's pretty cool.

V0405_33_00_01_0.text: You and I both know that you can't defeat me!

V0405_33_00_02_0.text: The Super Secret Number Card Investigation Club's in action!

V0405_30_00_02_0.text: The winner does the talkin' and the loser does the walkin'!

V0405_34_00_03_0.text: Yuma wouldn't give up, so neither will I!

V0405_34_00_04_0.text: I'm not as nice as you.

V0405_34_00_05_0.text: Oh, is that what you're gonna do?

V0405_34_00_06_0.text: Stop doin' moves that I can't predict!

V0405_34_00_07_0.text: Try playing with something other than Numbers!

V0405_34_00_08_0.text: That's a nice combo you have there!

V0405_36_00_00_0.text: You got this in the bag!

V0405_36_00_02_0.text:
My bad.
This is all my fault.

V0405_36_00_03_0.text: Don't let anything distract you, Yuma!

V0405_36_00_05_0.text:
Oh no!
Yuma's not skilled enough to turn this around!

V0405_36_00_06_0.text: I leave the rest to you, Tori!

V0405_26_00_02_0.text: Heh! Is that the best you got!
